      "label": "Transcript",
      "value": "Columbia 3rd Dec [1851]    Make me an offer of the medium between my price $85,000 and yours of $70,000- namely $77,500. and I will give you an answer as to whether I can entertain it-  Should I conclude, after mature reflection, to take the above offer, I think that I could arrange the payment over and above the debt to the Bank of Charleston, (which is already arranged for) in the following way- the balance will amount to the sum of $22,500, which may be paid upon the following terms- $10,000. in cash the balance $12,500. to be paid in three equal annual installments (interest added) of $4,133.33  D. H. Hamilton    To Jas. B. Heyward Esq."
    },
